verbose_text: Some of the major determinants of CF lung disease include a decreased airway surface liquid volume, increased mucus viscosity, chronic microbial colonisation, an impaired protease-antiprotease balance and increased pulmonary inflammation mediated in part by proinflammatory lipid- or collagen derived molecules such as ceramide and PGP.
